The paper focuses on text analysis approaches for a specialized search engine, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as text classification and named entity recognition. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computation and Language (cs.CL), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). However, since the paper specifically deals with NLP techniques for text classification and named entity recognition, we can prioritize cs.CL and cs.IR as the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.DL.
